.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "May 2026" "Version 1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic UNIX command interpreter that reads commands from standard input,
parses them, and executes programs by resolving their paths using the
.B PATH
environment variable. It supports both interactive (terminal) and
non-interactive (piped or script) modes.

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS

.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell. If no argument is provided, it exits with the status of the
last executed command.

.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment variables to standard output.

.SH EXAMPLES

.TP
.B pwd
Prints the absolute path of the current working directory.

.TP
.B echo Hello
Prints:
Hello

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns the exit status of the last executed command.
.br
Returns \fB127\fR if a command is not found.
.br
Returns \fB0\fR on success.

.SH NOTES
This shell is a simplified educational implementation of a UNIX command
interpreter. It does not aim to fully comply with POSIX shell standards.

.SH AUTHORS
Written by Shahad Alharbi and Basem Tashkandi as part of the Holberton School
simple shell project.

